hopobject.body: this post is fantastic manforce viagra tablets Still, while Moore is resuming his hockey career, he now has a mission off the ice: To remember Katie by helping others in her name. So he has started the Katie Moore Foundation (katiemoore.org), dedicated to helping patients and families with rare cancers through research, advocacy and community. The second annual Smashfest charity ping-pong event on July 25 in Toronto (smashfest.ca), attended by several NHL players, was started originally to benefit concussion research, but now also will benefit the Katie Moore Foundation.
